[{"id":"VR803428","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two metal spheres resting on insulating stands. The first sphere has a radius of uppercase R and the second sphere has a radius of 2 uppercase R.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR803428.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two metal spheres, Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> with radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase R\"><math alttext=\"uppercase R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> and Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> with radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 uppercase R\"><math alttext=\"2 uppercase R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></math></span></span>, rest on insulating stands. Both spheres carry an excess charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive uppercase Q\"><math alttext=\"positive uppercase Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mstyle></math></span></span>. The two spheres are briefly brought into contact, and are then separated. Which of the following correctly describes the resulting surface charge density, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"sigma sub 1\"><math alttext=\"sigma sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>σ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"sigma sub 2\"><math alttext=\"sigma sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>σ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, on each s